If this thing only activates when motor vehicles are present, and specifically does not activate for pedestrians…

what happens if we send out a big bunch of pedestrians, have them stand a few paces apart all the way down the road, and then send out a car?

Or what if we send out a very slow motor vehicle, slow enough that a human can keep pace with it the whole time?

What if we drill a hole in the gas tank so that the car runs out of fuel and can't enter any of the challenges? What if we build a car that operates on beamed power, and then cut the power?

Pretty obvious that bicycles wouldn't activate this… are horse-drawn carriages safe?

What if we secretly program the car with the route so that it drives itself, and the steering wheel is a placebo?







